WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.320 --> 00:00:11.200
Yoga for Peace - Nadi Shuddhi

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:16.020
Sadhguru: The word "Nadi Shuddhi" literally
means cleansing the nadis.

00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:17.620
[ There are 72000 pathways in the human system ]

00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:21.740
When we say nadis, we are not talking about
the 72,000,

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:27.840
because these 72,000 are only a branch out of the two basic nadis -

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.600
the pingala and the ida.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:35.680
36,000 branching out from pingala, 36,000 branching out from ida.

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:40.940
This is the energy physiology of a human being.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:47.000
When we say 'Nadi Shuddhi', we are talking about
cleansing fundamentally the pingala and ida

00:00:47.040 --> 00:00:50.800
so that energy system will work in balance.

00:00:51.040 --> 00:00:56.080
There is a connection between your breath
and your mental structure.

00:00:56.160 --> 00:01:01.600
To bring balance to your thought is a very
important step that you need to take,

00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:07.360
if you want to bring balance to your activity, your
emotion and the results of your life and

00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:09.920
the impact that you have on other peoples’ lives,

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:14.080
Nadi shuddhi plays an important role.

00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:18.720
Here are a few guidelines that will set optimal
conditions and

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:22.240
greatly enhance your receptivity of the practices.

00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:28.800
Please ensure cell phones are either in silent
mode or switched off.

00:01:28.800 --> 00:01:33.440
It is advisable not to sit for the program
with a full stomach

00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:34.720
or immediately after a meal.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:42.400
Please sit with your spine comfortably erect,
hands uncrossed and palms open.

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:47.200
These conditions will prepare you to be in
a heightened state of receptivity and

00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:51.000
derive the most benefits from the practices.

00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:56.160
These practices are very safe and simple and
can be done by anybody.

00:01:57.040 --> 00:02:06.000
The practices we will be learning here can
be done by anyone ages 7 years and above.

00:02:06.080 --> 00:02:12.000
If you wear glasses, while doing the yoga
practices, please remove them and keep them aside.

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:16.960
How to do Nadi Shuddhi – she will demonstrate,
please observe.

00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:24.000
Sit in a cross-legged posture with your spine
comfortably erect, eyes closed.

00:02:25.440 --> 00:02:30.960
Left hand should be loosely placed in
the middle of your lap, palm facing upwards.

00:02:31.100 --> 00:02:40.000
Use only your right hand, use your thumb and
ring finger, fold your middle and index fingers,

00:02:40.100 --> 00:02:44.000
The ring and little finger are held straight
and side-by-side touching.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:52.000
Now, block your right nostril with your thumb
and inhale through your left nostril.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
After the inhalation is complete, exhale through
the same.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:01.000
In a similar fashion, using the ring finger
block your left nostril

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:06.000
and inhale through your right nostril.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Then exhale through the same.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:19.000
Again block the right and open the left, inhale,
and exhale.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Continue like this.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Be focused on your breath.

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:31.900
So when you do this Nadi Shuddhi, what is most
important is, to breathe fully in, and fully out,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:35.900
as slowly and as gently as it is possible
for you.

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
You should not make any sound when you exhale
or inhale.

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:46.000
So for this to happen, you just need to remember
one basic point

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.920
so that Nadi Shuddhi happens by itself.

00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:53.920
You will always switch after every exhalation.

00:03:53.920 --> 00:04:01.200
So that means, whichever nostril you inhale
through, the same nostril you exhale through.

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:07.740
You do Nadi Shuddhi for a minimum of four
minutes.

00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:10.560
A few corrections for the practice

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:14.400
Do not keep your left hand on the thigh.

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:19.000
The left hand should be loosely placed in
the middle of your lap.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:23.680
To clarify, on the right hand, you use
only your thumb and ring finger.

00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:30.160
The ring and little finger are held straight
and are side by side touching.

00:04:30.160 --> 00:04:33.600
Fold your middle and index fingers.

00:04:33.680 --> 00:04:43.600
If you are unable to hold them straight, do
it as best as you can.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:05:01.040
Also, there is a tendency to keep the head
down or turned to one side.

00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:06.000
Unconsciously your face may tilt one way or the other.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:09.120
Your head should be straight.

00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:14.880
If you maintain this, your system will come
to a balance very quickly.

00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:20.000
Ensure not to press too hard on the lower
part of the nostril.

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.160
Locate the septal bone on your right nostril.

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:27.600
Just a millimeter beneath that, if you place the thumb,

00:05:27.600 --> 00:05:30.960
with very minimal pressure, you can
block the nostril effectively

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:34.000
so that no air can escape.

00:05:34.080 --> 00:05:40.960
Ensure you are not breathing shallow
doing normal breathing, or holding the breath.

00:05:40.960 --> 00:05:47.000
The breathing should be fully in and fully
out.

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:53.280
We will do Nadi Shuddhi together now.

00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:59.760
Sit in a cross-legged posture with
your spine comfortably erect.

00:05:59.760 --> 00:06:02.000
If you are unable to sit on the floor,

00:06:02.100 --> 00:06:08.000
You can sit in a chair with your legs crossed at the ankles.

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:15.680
Left hand should be loosely placed in
the middle of your lap, palm facing upwards.

00:06:15.680 --> 00:06:18.000
Use only your right hand.

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:24.000
Use your thumb and ring finger, fold your
middle and index fingers.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:30.000
The ring and little finger are held straight
and are side by side touching.

00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:32.960
Close your eyes.

00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:39.000
Now block your right nostril with your thumb,
and inhale through your left nostril.

00:06:39.040 --> 00:06:46.560
After the inhalation is complete, exhale through
the same.

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:53.920
Now using the ring finger, block your left
nostril and inhale through the right nostril.

00:06:53.920 --> 00:07:00.640
Then exhale through the same.

00:07:00.640 --> 00:07:09.440
Again block the right and open the
left. Inhale. And exhale.

00:07:09.440 --> 00:07:16.160
Continue to do this until we ask you to stop.

00:07:16.160 --> 00:07:22.480
Be focused on your breath.

00:07:22.480 --> 00:07:28.000
The breathing is fully in and fully out.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:37.120
Do it as slowly and gently as you can.

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:52.000
Make sure your spine is comfortably erect.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:06.000
Ensure your head is straight.

00:08:16.500 --> 00:08:20.000
Continue to be focused on your breath.

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:58.560
You can end with an exhalation through your left nostril and stop.

00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:08.000
Please slowly open your eyes.

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:12.320
[Explore 5 minutes for Peace] Sadhguru: Peace is not the ultimate goal of life.

00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:15.040
It is the most fundamental requirement.

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:22.240
If you hold it as the ultimate goal in your
life, you will only rest in peace.

